nd phrases such as “positive learning environment” or “negative learning environment” are commonly used in reference to the social and emotional dimensions of a school or class.</p>\r\n<p>For related discussions, see <a title=\"Learner\" href=\"https://www.edglossary.org/learner/\" class=\"ui-link\">learner</a>, <a title=\"Learning Experience\" href=\"https://www.edglossary.org/learning-experience/\" class=\"ui-link\">learning experience</a>, and <a title=\"Learning Pathway\" href=\"https://www.edglossary.org/learning-pathway/\" class=\"ui-link\">learning pathway</a>.</p>\r\n', 'Learning Environment', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-06-21 10:28:56', '2018-06-21 10:28:56', '', 6, 'http://localhost/working%20area/learning/index.php/2018/06/21/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
