(15, 1, '2018-06-21 10:50:28', '2018-06-21 10:50:28', '<b>Front</b>-<b>end</b> and back-<b>end</b> are terms used to characterize program interfaces and services relative to the initial user of these interfaces and services. (The \"user\" may be a human being or a program.) A \"<b>front</b>-<b>end</b>\" application is one that application users interact with directly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Front</b>-<b>end</b> and back-<b>end</b> are terms used to characterize program interfaces and services relative to the initial user of these interfaces and services. (The \"user\" may be a human being or a program.) A \"<b>front</b>-<b>end</b>\" application is one that application users interact with directly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Front</b>-<b>end</b> and back-<b>end</b> are terms used to characterize program interfaces and services relative to the initial user of these interfaces and services. (The \"user\" may be a human being or a program.) A \"<b>front</b>-<b>end</b>\" application is one that application users interact with directly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Front</b>-<b>end</b> and back-<b>end</b> are terms used to characterize program interfaces and services relative to the initial user of these interfaces and services. (The \"user\" may be a human being or a program.) A \"<b>front</b>-<b>end</b>\" application is one that application users interact with directly.', 'Services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'services', '', '', '2018-06-22 12:26:14', '2018-06-22 12:26:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/working%20area/learning/?page_id=15', 2, 'page', '', 0),
